== Icelandic. ==

noun, female gender, only singular.

English meaning: Inflection.

Stems from the words „fall“ (inflection case) and „beyging“ (in this case, meaning to inflect). Verb is A) fallbeygja, or B) beygja í föllum.


Inflection:

nominative: fallbeyging

accusative: fallbeygingu

dative: fallbeygingu

genitive: fallbeygingar


with definite article:

nom.: fallbeygingin

acc.: fallbeyginguna

dat.: fallbeygingunni

gen.: fallbeygingarinnar

